When would you want to use a remote repository rather than keeping all your work local?
Incase i cannot access my computer, i would use a remote repository

Why might you want to always pull changes manually rather than having Git
automatically stay up-to-date with your remote repository?
I may not want them locally included in my project

Describe the differences between forks, clones, and branches.
When would you use one instead of another?
Fork is copying someone`s project on their github account onto your
github account online.

clones: copying a repository onto your local machine

branches: the different segments of your project.

I would use fork on github, clone to copy a file to my local machine and
branches when i want to test out a new feature in my project.

What is the benefit of having a copy of the last known state of the remote
stored locally?
Helps in merging new files. you can easily find the differences.

How would you collaborate without using Git or GitHub? What would be easier,
and what would be harder?
I would hard to collaborate
